Full Title: Languages for Intercultural Dialogue 

Date: 07-Nov-2008 - 09-Nov-2008
Location: Nicosia, Cyprus 
Contact Person: Thekla Constantinou
Meeting Email: constantinou.thekla@ucy.ac.cy

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 30-Jun-2008 

Meeting Description:

The University of Cyprus (UCY) and the Ministry of Education and Culture (MOEC) are organizing a three-day event devoted to the teaching and learning of foreign languages at all levels of education.  The conference primarily aims to open a dialogue among all stakeholders on the current situation, the challenges and the prospects of language teaching in Cyprus.  Moreover, the conference will offer participants a wide variety of both practical and theoretical presentations and will consist of academic lectures, presentations by teachers, and workshops.   The event is organized within the framework of the European Year of Intercultural Dialogue.

L'Université de Chypre (UCY) et le Ministère de l'Éducation et de la Culture (MOEC) organisent un congrès de trois jours qui sera consacré à l'enseignement/ apprentissage des langues étrangères, à tous les niveaux du système scolaire/universitaire.  Le but est d'établir un dialogue entre tous les intéressés et de réfléchir aux défis et perspectives de l'enseignement des langues à Chypre à l'heure actuelle.  Le congrès  offrira aux participants une variété de présentations théoriques et appliquées. Elle comprendra des conférences, des communications faites par des chercheurs et des enseignants, et des ateliers.  Cette manifestation est organisée dans le cadre de l'année européenne pour le dialogue interculturel. 

Languages for Intercultural Dialogue

Papers in all areas of language teaching will be considered and especially in the following areas:

- EU Language Policies 
Common European Framework of Reference for Languages
European Language Portfolio
European Language Label
CLIL - Content Language Integrated Learning 
Europass
European Language Indicator
European Profile for language teachers
Profile of Language Education Policy
- Language Teaching and Learning (Pre-primary, Primary, Secondary, Tertiary)
- Professional Development, Lifelong Learning 
- Technology in Language Teaching 			
- Teacher Training (Pre-service, In service)
- Teaching Greek as a second/foreign language   		
- Language Teaching: Historical Perspectives
- Teaching Turkish as a second/foreign language 		
- The linguistic needs of migrant communities 
- Language Policy and Plurilingualism
 
The conference will be under the auspices of Mr Leonard Orban, EU Commissioner for Multilingualism.

The languages of the conference are Greek, English and French. Workshops and thematic units will be held in all the languages taught in the public sector:  English, French, German, Greek, Italian, Russian, Spanish, Turkish.

